<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0496 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Green Party explains why Britain must abandon all nuclear technologyfor weapons or electricity and suggests positive ways to make a saferworld for future generations. The argument is that the nuclear industrycauses pollution, danger and health risks and is not cheaper as claimedby the supporters of nuclear power. Figures are presented to illustratethis. Fallout from weapons testing and reactor accidents and environmentalcontamination from nuclear plants and waste are accused of causing deathsfrom leukaemia and cancer. The safety of nuclear plants is also questioned.The security measures and secretiveness of the nuclear industry is criticised.The consequences of a nuclear war are considered and the need for nuclearweapons challenged. Energy conservation and the use of renewable energysources are advocated instead of nuclear energy. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>